Adjust racks to top and middle positions and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Trim, peel, and cut @Carrots{12%oz} on a diagonal into 1⁄2-inch-thick pieces. Trim @Green Beans{6%oz} if necessary.

Toss carrots on one side of a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @Cooking Oil{1%tsp}, half the @Fry Seasoning{1%tbsp}, @Salt{}, and @Pepper{}.

Roast on top rack for ~{10%minutes} (you'll add the green beans then).

Meanwhile, pat @Chicken Cutlets{10%oz} dry with #paper towels{}; season with salt and pepper.

Place @Butter{1%tbsp} in a shallow #microwave-safe dish{}. Microwave until melted, ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in @Panko Breadcrumbs{1/4%cup}, @Frank's Seasoning Blend{1/4%oz}, and a pinch of salt and pepper.

Brush @Sour Cream{3%tbsp} onto tops of chicken in a thin layer. (You'll use the remaining sour cream in the next step.) Working one piece at a time, dip brushed sides of chicken into panko mixture, pressing to adhere (no need to coat the undersides).

Place chicken, coated sides up, on a second baking sheet.

Roast chicken on middle rack until browned and cooked through, ~{15-18%minutes}. Transfer to a #plate{} to rest.

While chicken cooks, in a #small bowl{}, combine @Blue Cheese Dressing{1.5%oz} and remaining sour cream. Season with salt and pepper.

Once carrots have roasted 10 minutes, remove sheet from oven. Carefully toss green beans on empty side with a drizzle of @Cooking Oil{1%tsp}, salt, and pepper.

Return sheet to top rack until carrots are browned and green beans are tender, ~{12-15%minutes}.

Divide carrots, green beans, and chicken between plates. Top chicken with blue cheese sauce and @?Hot Sauce{1%tsp} if desired. Serve with any remaining blue cheese sauce on the side.